description.narrative: The Pacific Agreement on Closer Economic Relations (PACER) Plus is a trade and development agreement negotiated between Australia, New Zealand and Forum Island Countries (FIC). This Readiness Package supports FICs' preparations to meet requirements to ratify the Agreement. This contributes to economic resilience by strengthening Pacific government services and capability in relation to trade (border management), international trade compliance, agriculture (biosecurity) and health (food safety).
